<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
The single female from this study matches the general morphology of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Hygrobates" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hygrobates microepimeratus" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microepimeratus">Hygrobates microepimeratus</taxonomicName>
(Sokolow, 1934) a species described from the Primory Territory in the Russian Far East (
<bibRefCitation author="Sokolow, I" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Jahrbuecher, Abteilung fuer Systematik, Oekologie und Geographie der Tiere" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="309 - 388" title="Beitraege zur Kenntnis der Hydracarinenfauna des Ussuri Gebietes II. Hydracarinen der fliessenden Gewaesser." volume="65" year="1934">Sokolow 1934</bibRefCitation>
), and later on reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chung, K-S" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural Sciences Research of the Institute KANU" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="117 - 135" title="Eight species of water mites (Acari) new to Korean fauna." volume="13" year="1997">Chung and Kim (1997)</bibRefCitation>
from Korea. This species is known from a female only making it difficult to separate from other similar species, i.e. 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Hygrobates" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hygrobates ezoensis" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ezoensis">Hygrobates ezoensis</taxonomicName>
Uchida, 1934 (Russia: Sakhalin, Japan: Hokkaido) and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Hygrobates" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hygrobates taniguchii" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taniguchii">Hygrobates taniguchii</taxonomicName>
Imamura, 1954 (Japan, Hokkaido). In the original description 
<bibRefCitation author="Sokolow, I" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Jahrbuecher, Abteilung fuer Systematik, Oekologie und Geographie der Tiere" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="309 - 388" title="Beitraege zur Kenntnis der Hydracarinenfauna des Ussuri Gebietes II. Hydracarinen der fliessenden Gewaesser." volume="65" year="1934">Sokolow (1934</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sokolow, I" journalOrPublisher="Edition de l'Academie des Sciences de l' URSS, Moscou-Leningrad" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" title="Hydracarina (1 re partie: Hydrachnellae). Faune de l'URSS. Arachnides" year="1940">1940</bibRefCitation>
), in addition to more slender P-3 (compared with 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Hygrobates" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hygrobates diversiporus" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diversiporus">Hygrobates diversiporus</taxonomicName>
), gave particular weight to the smaller dimensions of coxae which occupy one third of venter. According to 
<bibRefCitation pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Imamura (1954)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Hygrobates" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hygrobates taniguchii" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taniguchii">Hygrobates taniguchii</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Hygrobates" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hygrobates microepimeratus" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microepimeratus">Hygrobates microepimeratus</taxonomicName>
in larger coxae. 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Hygrobates" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hygrobates ezoensis" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ezoensis">Hygrobates ezoensis</taxonomicName>
differs in P-2 with a more pronounced and acute ventrodistal projection and stouter P-3 (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Matsumoto, N" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="1893 - 1945" title="Water mites of the genus Hygrobates Koch, 1837 (Acari: Parasitengona: Hygrobatidae) from Hokkaido, northern Japan." url="10.1080/00222930400023727" volume="39" year="2005">Matsumoto et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
